==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|consumpcion|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|consumptio|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/kənˈsʌmp.ʃən/}}
* {{audio|en-us-consumption.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# The act of [[consume|consuming]] something.
#: ''The fire's '''consumption''' of the forest caused ecological changes.''
# The amount [[consume|consumed]].
#: ''gross national '''consumption'''''
# {{context|pathology|lang=en}} The [[waste away|wasting-away]] of the human body through [[disease]].
# {{senseid|en|TB}}{{context|pathology|dated|lang=en}} [[pulmonary tuberculosis|Pulmonary tuberculosis]].

